@full_implementation
title: Full Implementation
on-arrival: budget -= 2; reformer_approval += 4; moderate_approval += 1; hardliner_approval -= 4

We allow truly competitive elections, permitting opposition figures and non-Party candidates to run. This is a major step toward democracy but severely weakens Party control, emboldening regional nationalists and reformists.

@controlled_elections
title: Controlled Elections 
on-arrival: budget -= 1; reformer_approval += 2; moderate_approval += 2; hardliner_approval -= 2

We introduce multi-candidate elections but restrict candidacy to Communist Party members and loyal figures. This gives the appearance of democracy while maintaining stability.

@undermine_elections
title: Undermine Elections 
on-arrival: budget -= 1; reformer_approval -= 2; hardliner_approval += 2

We allow elections but manipulate the process, ensuring that Communist Party candidates dominate the results. This preserves Party authority but discredits reforms and increases public cynicism.

@delay_elections
title: Delay Elections 
on-arrival: budget += 1; reformer_approval -= 3; hardliner_approval += 4

We postpone competitive elections indefinitely, citing instability and the need for further preparation. This maintains order but alienates reformists and sparks protests.
